{"key":"processedPost-12328580","value":{"id":12328580,"first":12327900,"last":12337403,"when":1270403009,"utime":"04/04/10 08:43 PM","content":"Thanks for the tip, but since one mists from the very first day cakes are added, the proper frequency of misting keeps the perlite hydrated and it doesn't dry out.&nbsp; I've gone months without re-soaking the perlite and had upper 90% humidity the whole time.&nbsp; The key is misting.&nbsp; Fresh air dries out the substrate <i>and</i> the perlite, both of which are then replenished by frequent misting.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of substrate moisture content is a major pinning trigger.<br />RR","title":"Re: Maintaining Humidity?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}